---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "About Us | Pallets Pallets Pallets — Atlanta";
const description =
  "Pallets, Pallets, Pallets is an Atlanta-based wooden pallet supplier and recycler. Family-run, Owner Partners on the yard, no middlemen, no surprises.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} path="/about">
  <section class="bg-pallet-cream py-16 sm:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-pallet-wood mb-3">About</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-pallet-wood-dark mb-4">
        Family-run, owner-on-the-yard.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-stone-700">
        Pallets, Pallets, Pallets is an Atlanta-based wooden-pallet operation run by Owner Partners who actually answer the phone. When you call, you get someone with skin in the game — not a call center.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 space-y-6 text-stone-700 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        We started with a simple read on the Atlanta market: warehouses pay too much for new pallets when good remanufactured units are available, and they spend too much manpower on broken pallets piling up out back. Both problems get solved when one operator handles both ends — and that's the operation we built.
      </p>

      <p>
        Today, we supply new and reclaimed pallets across the metro Atlanta region and pull broken or surplus units from your dock as fast as we can route a truck. The same pickup that hauls away your dead pallets becomes the supply for someone else's standing order, two days later, after a turn through our repair bench. Less waste, less cost, less drama.
      </p>

      <p>
        We're not the biggest operator in town and we don't try to be. We're small enough that the Owner Partners know every account, big enough to handle full-trailer volume, and stubborn enough about quality that our repeat-customer rate is the metric we actually care about.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pallet-wood-dark mt-12 mb-4">How we work</h2>

      <ul class="space-y-3">
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-pallet-wood font-bold mt-1" aria-hidden="true">1.</span>
          <span><strong>Call or email.</strong> Tell us what you have on the dock, what you need delivered, or both. Rough quantities are fine — we'll dial it in.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-pallet-wood font-bold mt-1" aria-hidden="true">2.</span>
          <span><strong>Quote &amp; schedule.</strong> Same-business-day response with a price and a window.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-pallet-wood font-bold mt-1" aria-hidden="true">3.</span>
          <span><strong>We show up.</strong> Truck, driver, hand pallet jack as needed. We work clean and move quick.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-pallet-wood font-bold mt-1" aria-hidden="true">4.</span>
          <span><strong>Standing accounts get easier over time.</strong> Once we know your dock and your rhythm, scheduling drops to a text message.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-pallet-cream py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pallet-wood-dark mb-4">Ready when you are.</h2>
      <a
        href="/contact"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-pallet-wood text-pallet-cream px-6 py-3 rounded-md font-semibold hover:bg-pallet-wood-dark transition-colors"
      >
        Get in touch
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
